# Authoring rules for voices configuration

- PURPOSE: Keep `src/voices.json` consistent when adding or editing voice lines.

- FILE: `src/voices.json`
  - Root:
    {
      "voices": [ CategoryObject, ... ]
    }
  - CategoryObject:
    {
      "categoryName": string,
      "categoryDescription": { "en-US": string, "zh-CN": string },
      "voiceList": [ VoiceObject, ... ]
    }
  - VoiceObject:
    {
      "name": string,
      "path": string,  // exact filename including extension
      "description": {
        "en-US": string,
        "zh-CN": string,
        "ja-JP"?: string
      }
    }

- STYLE:
  - Indentation: two spaces. Keep field order: name → path → description. No trailing commas on final items.
  - Preserve full-width punctuation/emoji as-is (e.g. （ ）！~ ↗). Do not ASCII-normalize.

- ADDING NEW VOICES:
  - Default category: append to `2025小岁` → `voiceList` unless otherwise specified.
  - Keep insertion order identical to the user’s provided list.
  - `path` must exactly equal the audio filename (including `.MP3`). Do not escape, rename, or change case.
  - `description.zh-CN`: mirror `name` by default.
  - `description.en-US`: concise natural-English gloss; if unclear, mirror or transliterate.
  - `description.ja-JP`: provide brief Japanese gloss when possible; if unclear, mirror or transliterate.

- NEW CATEGORY (when requested):
  {
    "categoryName": "<name>",
    "categoryDescription": { "en-US": "<en>", "zh-CN": "<zh>" },
    "voiceList": [ /* VoiceObject items */ ]
  }

- VALIDATION BEFORE COMMIT:
  - JSON is valid; no linter errors.
  - Each voice has `name`, `path`, and `description` with at least `en-US` and `zh-CN`.
  - `path` strings match actual files in assets exactly (including extension).
  - Indentation and commas conform to file style.

- EXAMPLE (exact order and indentation):
  {
    "name": "注意闪光",
    "path": "注意闪光.MP3",
    "description": {
      "en-US": "Watch the flash",
      "zh-CN": "注意闪光",
      "ja-JP": "フラッシュ注意"
    }
  }
